api-1  | Essays
api-1  | What excites you about a career in engineering/technology? Why do you think your abilities and skills are a good fit for
api-1  | Plaksha's B.Tech program?
api-1  | On 25th February 2017, I watched Marvel Studios' Iron Man for the first time. Witnessing Jarvis, Tony Stark's AI assistant capable of executing
api-1  | complex tasks through voice commands, sparked my curiosity and determination to create something game-changing. I went on to research
api-1  | and realized humanity is still far from achieving transformative technologies that could redefine our reality. This realization sparked my
api-1  | journey into technology and innovation. My academic pursuits have focused on the theoretical applications of these fields, while my personal
api-1  | projects reflect my passion for bridging technology with everyday life. From a young age, I've been passionate about Mathematics,
api-1  | participating in interschool Math contests as early as grade 5. This journey has helped me cultivate strong logical thinking, and I aim to
api-1  | combine these skills with my attitude of continuous learning, growth & innovation, contributing meaningfully to the technological
api-1  | advancements shaping our future. My problem-solving skills have developed through consistent effort and practice, as reflected in my
api-1  | academic journey and exams like the Math & Physics Olympiads, which require analytical thinking and perseverance. Mathematics and
api-1  | Computer Science have helped me tackle complex problems under time constrain, reinforcing my ability to work under pressure with a
api-1  | solution-oriented mindset. During my high school years, I undertook various projects that enhanced my understanding of programming
api-1  | languages and algorithms. I designed a code that could encrypt and decrypt texts adopting unique algorithms each time (which I now
api-1  | personally use as a brain-teaser). Though rudimentary compared to Jarvis, it has been a motivating step towards my vision of creating
api-1  | impactful technology. Beyond academics, I have actively participated in STEM and leadership activities. As Head Boy of my school, I had the
api-1  | opportunity to contribute to initiatives that combined leadership with technological innovation, such as implementing digital tools to improve
api-1  | project management. These experiences taught me the importance of collaboration and leadership in bringing ideas to life. I have also
api-1  | developed several Science models reflecting my dedication to creating innovative solutions. To broaden my knowledge and skill-set, I
api-1  | undertook an internship at AccelEd, a career counseling firm, where I contributed as a content writer, web-developer, and video editor. This
api-1  | experience helped me gain knowledge of applications of software in the industry. My extracurricular activities have positively affected my
api-1  | personality and work ethic. As an avid guitarist, I've developed creativity and precision, which I apply to my software projects. Representing
api-1  | my school in sports (athletics) at various levels helped me learn discipline, teamwork, and perseverance, all crucial for success in technology.
api-1  | These experiences have given me an all-round perspective, enabling me to approach software development with both, technical and creative
api-1  | approaches. With this holistic approach, I am keen to contribute to and grow within leading universities. In conclusion, my journey from being
api-1  | inspired by Tony Stark's Jarvis to pursuing innovation has been one of continuous learning.
api-1  | Share a time when you contributed to a project or activity that positively affected your school or community. What
api-1  | challenges did you face, and what did you learn about leadership and perseverance?
